+{"id":"frankenredis-3g0p","title":"s5su part b: upstream-compatible listpack decoder primitive (fr-persist::listpack)","description":"Implements a standalone listpack decoder used by s5su-c/d + v8s5-c. Accepts upstream listpack byte sequences and returns Vec<Vec<u8>> entries.\n\nScope:\n  * Listpack header: total-bytes (u32 LE) + num-elements (u16 LE).\n  * Per-entry encoding: 7-bit uint / 6-bit str / 12-bit str / 13-bit int / 16-bit int / 24-bit int / 32-bit int / 64-bit int / 32-bit str + back-ref byte.\n  * End-of-listpack 0xFF terminator check.\n  * Unit tests with hand-crafted listpack bytes covering every encoding branch.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:17:58.100575904Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:21:35.308350576Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:21:35.305784776Z","close_reason":"Landed in 270414d: pub mod fr_persist::listpack with forward-iterating decoder over every upstream encoding branch (7-bit uint, 6/12/32-bit str, 13/16/24/32/64-bit signed int) + backlen skip + terminator validation. 12 unit tests covering happy paths and malformed-input rejection. Consumed by s5su-c (hjub), s5su-d (qi6z), s5su-e (6zk9), v8s5-c (hycu). No encoder yet — that lands in 6zk9.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
