 {"id":"frankenredis-jrki","title":"redis parity: FUNCTION admin subcommands should reject script context","description":"Vendored Redis marks FUNCTION LIST, STATS, LOAD, DELETE, DUMP, FLUSH, KILL, and RESTORE as NOSCRIPT in legacy_redis_code/redis/src/commands/function-list.json, function-stats.json, function-load.json, function-delete.json, function-dump.json, function-flush.json, function-kill.json, and function-restore.json. The local function_cmd implementation at crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:6145-6395 serves those subcommands without any script_nesting_level guard today. Add Redis-compatible NOSCRIPT handling while preserving the current arity and syntax validation order, and cover the admin subcommand matrix from Lua.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:04:38.507997412Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T07:39:46.110193356Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T07:39:46.108044097Z","close_reason":"Completed by existing implementation in frankenredis-qxja","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-jsr7","title":"HIGH: CLUSTER admin subcommands + READONLY/READWRITE always return 'cluster support disabled' regardless of cluster_enabled","description":"## Summary\n\n`crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:6007-6021` routes fifteen CLUSTER admin subcommands to the `cluster_disabled_error()` path unconditionally:\n\n```rust\nif sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"RESET\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"MEET\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"FORGET\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"REPLICATE\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"REPLICAS\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"FAILOVER\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"ADDSLOTS\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"DELSLOTS\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"ADDSLOTSRANGE\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"DELSLOTSRANGE\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"FLUSHSLOTS\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"SAVECONFIG\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"SET-CONFIG-EPOCH\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"BUMPEPOCH\\\")\n    || sub.eq_ignore_ascii_case(\\\"SLOTSTATE\\\")\n{\n    return Err(cluster_disabled_error());\n}\n```\n\nThe error message is \\\"ERR This instance has cluster support disabled\\\" — but the check does not consult `store.cluster_enabled`, so this error is returned even when the operator has set `cluster-enabled yes`.\n\nREADONLY and READWRITE at lines 6115-6131 are even blunter:\n\n```rust\nfn readonly_cmd(argv: &[Vec<u8>]) -> Result<RespFrame, CommandError> {\n    if argv.len() != 1 { return Err(CommandError::WrongArity(\\\"READONLY\\\")); }\n    Err(CommandError::Custom(\n        \\\"ERR This instance has cluster support disabled\\\".to_string(),\n    ))\n}\nfn readwrite_cmd(argv: &[Vec<u8>]) -> Result<RespFrame, CommandError> { /* same */ }\n```\n\nThey never check `cluster_enabled` at all. When cluster is enabled (MYID/SHARDS/KEYSLOT all respond with real data), a client that says `READONLY` to route reads to a replica still gets this misleading error.\n\n## Why it's a mock-code-finder catch\n\nIt fits the pattern's definition of a stub: short function, returns the same string regardless of input, callers (orchestrators, `redis-cli --cluster`) depend on real output but never get it. The stub takes the form of a *plausible error* rather than `todo!()`, which is exactly what made grep's first pass miss it — one has to trace through the conditional tree to find that the predicate never fires for real.\n\n## Impact\n\n- Any client that autodetects cluster mode via `CLUSTER INFO` + cluster_enabled_flag and then issues `CLUSTER MEET` to add a node sees a nonsensical \\\"disabled\\\" error when the server just told it cluster WAS enabled.\n- `redis-cli --cluster create` cannot configure FrankenRedis nodes into a cluster.\n- `redis-cli --cluster reshard` cannot move slots.\n- Primary/replica replacement via `CLUSTER FAILOVER` is not available.\n- Read-your-replica scale-out via `READONLY` is not available.\n\n## Applying /testing-conformance-harnesses\n\nPattern 4 matrix of (cluster_enabled, subcommand, expected_error_class):\n\n| cluster_enabled | subcommand | current reply | upstream reply | verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| false | MEET host port | `ERR ... cluster support disabled` | same | PASS |\n| true  | MEET host port | `ERR ... cluster support disabled` | attempts contact, returns OK or timeout | **FAIL** |\n| true  | ADDSLOTS 0 1 2 | `ERR ... cluster support disabled` | `OK` or `ERR Slot X is already busy` | **FAIL** |\n| true  | FAILOVER       | `ERR ... cluster support disabled` | `OK` (triggers election) or `ERR You should send CLUSTER FAILOVER to a replica` | **FAIL** |\n| any   | READONLY       | `ERR ... cluster support disabled` | in cluster mode: `OK`; outside: `ERR` | **FAIL** on cluster_enabled=true |\n\n## Fix direction\n\nTwo-pronged:\n\n1. **Correctness layer.** Add a `cluster_enabled` guard to READONLY/READWRITE, and split the 15-subcommand short-circuit into a real dispatch. For every admin subcommand, return either the correct OK/response OR a specific, upstream-shaped error (e.g. `ERR CLUSTER SETSLOT slot X node Y failed: Unknown node ID`), not the blanket \\\"disabled\\\" string. Start with arity + syntax errors matching upstream wording; behavioural work lands later.\n2. **Fuzzing layer.** Extend `fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_command_option_parsers.rs` (or a new `fuzz_cluster_admin_cmds.rs`) with structure-aware generation of all 15 admin commands × both cluster_enabled states; assert the reply category is never the blanket \\\"disabled\\\" string unless cluster_enabled=false.\n\n## Related\n\n- Depends on a real `fr-repl::ClusterState` with a slot map + node map (does not exist yet — separate bead to file if this grows).\n- Builds on `frankenredis-s5su` (RDB for clustered state), `frankenredis-jqgv` (WAIT).\n- Interacts with `frankenredis-1749` (differential fuzzer) — that fuzzer should opt-in cluster_enabled=true for half of its cases once this is fixed, otherwise it XFAILs every cluster-path divergence.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Matrix: every (cluster_enabled, subcommand) cell differential-matches upstream on at minimum: arity, syntax, unknown-subcommand wording.\n- READONLY + READWRITE return OK when cluster_enabled and the client is not in a transaction.\n- A shell loop of `redis-cli --cluster check 127.0.0.1:<our_port>` against a 3-node FrankenRedis cluster reports no unexpected errors for topology-read operations.\n\n## Labels\n\nfr-command, cluster, readonly, readwrite, misleading-error, conformance-gap, mock-finder","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T03:55:02.994069563Z","created_by":"cc-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-23T22:47:25.032795547Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T22:47:25.030853252Z","close_reason":"Closed with be0d91c (+ earlier c122714 READONLY/READWRITE): first-pass implementation of 13 CLUSTER admin subcommands with upstream-matching arity, syntax, and cluster_enabled gating. 3 new tests + 609/0 in fr-command --lib. SET-CONFIG-EPOCH and SLOTSTATE still blanket-errored pending real fr-repl config-epoch + slot-state machinery (not a 60-min scope).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cluster","conformance-gap","fr-command","misleading-error","mock-finder","readonly","readwrite"]}
