 {"id":"frankenredis-jzs","title":"Centralize version string as single const across all crates","description":"## Problem\n\nThe Redis version string appears in multiple locations:\n- fr-command/src/lib.rs: \\\"redis_version:7.2.0-frankenredis\\\" (INFO)\n- fr-runtime/src/lib.rs: hello_bulk(\\\"7.2.0\\\") (HELLO response)\n- fr-runtime/src/lib.rs: (\\\"redis-ver\\\", \\\"7.2.0\\\") (RDB aux field — was 7.0.0, fixed to 7.2.0 in f8c5a8a)\n\nWhile these are now consistent (all 7.2.0), there's no single source of truth. If the version needs to change, all three locations must be found and updated.\n\n## Fix\n\n1. Define a const in fr-runtime (or a shared crate): pub const REDIS_COMPAT_VERSION: &str = \\\"7.2.0\\\";\n2. Use this const in all locations\n3. Consider also deriving the FrankenRedis version from Cargo.toml via env!(\\\"CARGO_PKG_VERSION\\\")\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n- crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs: Define const, use in RDB and HELLO\n- crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs: Use const in INFO","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:11:03.925020086Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T03:34:50.855981956Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T03:34:50.854614367Z","close_reason":"Centralized REDIS_COMPAT_VERSION const in fr-store, used by fr-command INFO and fr-runtime HELLO/RDB","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
