 {"id":"frankenredis-qhid","title":"Implement metatables (getmetatable/setmetatable) for Lua 5.1 compatibility","description":"# Lua Metatables\n\n## What\nMetatables are a key Lua 5.1 feature. Some Redis Lua scripts use them for operator overloading or custom table behavior. Currently missing from the hand-written interpreter.\n\n## Why\nWhile rare in typical Redis scripts, metatables are part of the Lua 5.1 spec. Their absence could break third-party Lua libraries that depend on them.\n\n## Implementation\n1. Add a metatable field to LuaTable\n2. Implement getmetatable()/setmetatable() global functions\n3. Implement __index, __newindex, __tostring, __eq, __lt, __le, __add, __sub, __mul, __div, __mod, __pow, __concat, __len, __call metamethods\n4. Dispatch to metamethods when operations fail on the base table\n\n## Scope\nThis is significant work (~200-400 lines). Prioritize __index and __tostring as they are most commonly used.\n\n## Files\n- crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:13:08.354875762Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T20:10:45.092683154Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T20:10:45.092404106Z","close_reason":"Implemented getmetatable/setmetatable with real metatable storage (Option<LuaTable> in LuaTableInner). Added __index metamethod support via get_with_index() for table subscript, field access, and method calls. Supports chained __index (table→table). Added 5 tests covering get/set, __index fallback, chain, priority, and nil removal.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenredis-qi6z","title":"s5su part d: stream decoder extensions for LISTPACKS_2 (19) + LISTPACKS_3 (21) — consumer groups + seen/active times","description":"Extend the s5su-c decoder to parse consumer-group + consumer + PEL state from upstream type-19 and type-21 stream records. Populates the groups vec on RdbValue::Stream.\n\nNote on type tag collision: RDB_TYPE_HASH_WITH_TTLS is currently 21 (set in rv89/th7q, 25d6a64). This conflicts with upstream's RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS_3 which is also 21. Options:\n  * Option A: Shift our internal HashWithTtls to a reserved range (e.g., 100+) so upstream 21 can be our decoder-only stream path.\n  * Option B: Keep our internal 21 for hash; upstream interop only ever reads types 15/19 (losing LISTPACKS_3-specific features when ingesting 21-tagged streams from real Redis).\n\nPlan: adopt Option A. Revise th7q's type byte to 100, document the change, re-run th7q tests. Then use 21 exclusively for the stream decoder in upstream-produced files.\n\nBlocks s5su-e.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:17:24.348682901Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:17:24.348682901Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
