-{"id":"frankenredis-s5su","title":"HIGH: RDB type 15 (stream) encoding diverges from upstream — file interchange broken","description":"## Summary\n\nOur `fr-persist` serializes streams under RDB type byte 15 (our historical assignment), but upstream uses a different layout under the same tag plus a family of additional tags for consumer group state. Project memory note `project_rdb_stream_incompatibility.md`: \\\"RDB type 15 stream encoding differs from Redis, breaking file interchange\\\".\n\nImpact: any user who takes an upstream `dump.rdb` and boots our server on it gets a parse failure or (worse) silently-truncated stream state. Symmetrically, our RDB cannot be loaded by upstream. That violates AGENTS.md Compatibility Doctrine strict mode, which promises \\\"maximize observable compatibility for V1-scoped APIs\\\" with \\\"no behavior-altering repairs\\\".\n\n## Surface to verify\n\nUpstream `rdb.h` / `rdb.c` (see `legacy_redis_code/redis/src/rdb.h` and `rdb.c`):\n\n- `RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS` (15) — listpack-bodied stream\n- `RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS_2` (19) — adds per-consumer seen_time\n- `RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS_3` (21) — adds per-consumer active_time (7.2+)\n\nEach shape writes:\n1. radix tree: (stream-id, listpack)\n2. stream metadata: length, last_id, first_id, max_deleted_id, entries_added\n3. per consumer group: name, last_id, PEL size, PEL entries, consumer list\n4. per consumer: name, seen_time (v2+), active_time (v3+), pending entry IDs\n\nOur encoder should write v3 by default (matches upstream 7.2+) and decode all three.\n\n## Applying /testing-conformance-harnesses + /testing-fuzzing\n\n**Conformance (Pattern 3: cross-impl round-trip):**\n- Fixture corpus: 20 upstream-produced `.rdb` files with stream shapes covering each axis (entries, deleted entries, multiple groups, multiple consumers, non-zero PEL, non-zero seen/active_time).\n- Round-trip gate:\n  1. `fr-persist::rdb::decode(bytes)` must succeed on every fixture.\n  2. Re-encode; feed to upstream `redis-server --loadrdb`, query `XINFO STREAM FULL`; canonicalize and compare to our canonicalized `XINFO STREAM FULL` post-load.\n  3. Reverse: encode our in-memory stream, have upstream load it, compare stream state vector.\n\n**Fuzzing (/testing-fuzzing, structure-aware):**\n- Extend the existing `fuzz_rdb_structured.rs` with a stream-producing `arbitrary::Arbitrary` generator: random entries, groups, PELs. Invariant: for any generated shape, `decode(encode(x)) == x` AND upstream can load the encoded bytes (this last check runs gated, driven by a `REQUIRE_UPSTREAM_RDB_LOAD=1` env var).\n- Extend `fuzz_rdb_decoder.rs` with upstream-produced corpus (minimized from the 20 fixtures above) so crashes on adversarial streams are found quickly.\n\n## Related\n\n- Frames our broader persistence story for streams; the `core_stream.json` conformance fixtures already exist (`crates/fr-conformance/fixtures/core_stream.json`, 114 KB).\n- Does not depend on (but complements) frankenredis-rv89 (hash field TTL) and frankenredis-0zyf (fr-protocol conformance). All three share the upstream-fixture harvesting infra.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- 20/20 upstream fixtures decode cleanly.\n- Round-trip through upstream yields `XINFO STREAM FULL` identity for every fixture.\n- Fuzz target logs zero crashes / zero mismatches over 1M iterations.\n\n## Labels\n\nfr-persist, rdb, streams, conformance-gap, file-interchange, testing-conformance-harnesses","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T03:30:14.504545661Z","created_by":"cc-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-23T03:30:14.504545661Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance-gap","file-interchange","fr-persist","rdb","streams","testing-conformance-harnesses"]}
