+{"id":"frankenredis-v4x3","title":"CRITICAL: WrongSubcommandArity emits 'subcommand' suffix; upstream Redis 7.2.4 emits 'command' — two tests fail","description":"## Summary\n\n`cargo test --workspace` fails on main (HEAD eb6b915) with two assertions about the wording of `WrongSubcommandArity`. Our implementation special-cases `acl | slowlog | xgroup | xinfo` so the error ends with `subcommand` instead of `command`. A live probe against the vendored `legacy_redis_code/redis` binary (version 7.2.4, also reconfirmed against 7.4.8 per prior `PINNED 2026-04-22` comments in `fr-command`) shows upstream always ends the string with `command`. Our code is the divergence.\n\n## Failing tests\n\n- `fr-command` lib tests:\n  - `lua_eval::tests::acl_admin_subcommands_reject_from_scripts_after_validation`\n    - got: `ERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|whoami' subcommand`\n    - expected: `ERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|whoami' command`\n  - `tests::wrong_subcommand_arity_formats_redis_families_with_expected_wording`\n    - got: `ERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|setuser' subcommand`\n    - expected: `ERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|setuser' command`\n\n## Live oracle probe (redis_version 7.2.4)\n\n```\n$ redis-cli ACL WHOAMI extra\nERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|whoami' command\n\n$ redis-cli ACL SETUSER\nERR wrong number of arguments for 'acl|setuser' command\n\n$ redis-cli XGROUP CREATE\nERR wrong number of arguments for 'xgroup|create' command\n\n$ redis-cli XINFO STREAM\nERR wrong number of arguments for 'xinfo|stream' command\n```\n\nUpstream source `legacy_redis_code/redis/src/server.c:3792`:\n```c\n*err = sdscatprintf(*err, \"wrong number of arguments for '%s' command\", c->cmd->fullname);\n```\nand `acl.c:3033`:\n```c\naddReplyErrorFormat(c, \"wrong number of arguments for '%s' command\", cmd->fullname);\n```\nThe suffix is unconditionally `\"command\"`; there is no `\"subcommand\"` suffix anywhere.\n\n## Where it comes from\n\n`crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs:685-691`:\n```rust\nlet kind = match cmd_lower.as_str() {\n    \"acl\" | \"slowlog\" | \"xgroup\" | \"xinfo\" => \"subcommand\",\n    _ => \"command\",\n};\nRespFrame::Error(format!(\n    \"ERR wrong number of arguments for '{}|{}' {}\",\n    cmd_lower, sub_lower, kind\n))\n```\n\nThe special-case branch fires for every subcommand of ACL/SLOWLOG/XGROUP/XINFO. This includes at least 15 `WrongSubcommandArity` call sites scattered through `fr-command` (5145..5427, 6258..10729, etc.), all of which now emit the wrong string on the wire.\n\nGit log shows this was touched by `993bfb0 fix(command): use Redis command wording for subcommand arity` and `8f3ee5d fix(command): distinguish subcommand vs command in wrong-arity errors; FUNCTION STATS shape fixes` — the \"distinguish\" commit re-introduced the divergence that the earlier \"use Redis wording\" commit had removed.\n\n## Suggested fix direction\n\nCollapse the match to always emit `\"command\"`. The whole `kind` variable can go; the format string becomes:\n```rust\nformat!(\"ERR wrong number of arguments for '{cmd_lower}|{sub_lower}' command\")\n```\nNo call-site changes needed. The existing two tests already assert the correct string.\n\n## Labels\n\nci · tests · fr-command · conformance · acl · arity · upstream-divergence","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T03:25:06.444977185Z","created_by":"cc-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-23T17:06:46.988465674Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T17:06:46.986711733Z","close_reason":"Fixed in 212bcb8 — collapsed WrongSubcommandArity suffix match to unconditional 'command' per upstream Redis 7.2.4/7.4 behavior.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["acl","arity","ci","conformance","fr-command","tests","upstream-divergence"]}
 {"id":"frankenredis-v7zc","title":"Add pub/sub cross-client integration test via TCP","description":"# Pub/Sub Cross-Client TCP Test\n\n## What\nAn integration test that demonstrates pub/sub message delivery between multiple TCP clients connected to FrankenRedis.\n\n## Why\nPub/sub delivery is tested via internal APIs (conformance fixtures) but never through actual independent TCP connections. A subscriber on one connection must receive messages published from a completely separate connection.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Test 1: Basic Pub/Sub\n1. Start frankenredis on random port\n2. Client A (thread 1): SUBSCRIBE channel1, wait for subscription confirmation\n3. Client B (thread 2): PUBLISH channel1 \"hello\" → verify returns 1 (one subscriber)\n4. Client A: Read next message, verify [\"message\", \"channel1\", \"hello\"]\n5. Client A: UNSUBSCRIBE channel1\n\n### Test 2: Pattern Subscribe\n1. Client A: PSUBSCRIBE \"news.*\"\n2. Client B: PUBLISH news.sports \"goal!\" → returns 1\n3. Client A: Verify [\"pmessage\", \"news.*\", \"news.sports\", \"goal!\"]\n\n### Test 3: Multiple Subscribers\n1. Client A: SUBSCRIBE channel1\n2. Client C: SUBSCRIBE channel1\n3. Client B: PUBLISH channel1 \"broadcast\" → returns 2\n4. Both A and C receive the message\n\n### Test 4: Unsubscribe stops delivery\n1. Client A: SUBSCRIBE channel1\n2. Client B: PUBLISH channel1 \"msg1\" → A receives\n3. Client A: UNSUBSCRIBE channel1\n4. Client B: PUBLISH channel1 \"msg2\" → returns 0 (no subscribers)\n\n## Logging\n- Log all pub/sub operations with timestamps\n- Log message received events: \"[ClientA] RECEIVED: message channel1 hello\"\n- Log subscriber counts on PUBLISH\n\n## Files\n- crates/fr-server/tests/pubsub_e2e.rs (new)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:12:21.136076437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T19:05:42.368395054Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T19:05:42.368142626Z","close_reason":"Added 3 pub/sub E2E tests to tcp_e2e_test.rs: tcp_pubsub_basic_cross_client_delivery (subscribe/publish/unsubscribe lifecycle), tcp_pubsub_multiple_subscribers (broadcast to 2 clients), tcp_pubsub_pattern_subscribe (PSUBSCRIBE with pmessage delivery). All pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"frankenredis-v8s5","title":"HIGH: DUMP/RESTORE use frankenredis-private encoding — MIGRATE interop with upstream Redis impossible","description":"## Summary\n\n`Store::dump_key` at `crates/fr-store/src/lib.rs:9433-9511` emits a payload using a **frankenredis-internal** type-byte scheme and length encoding, not the upstream RDB format. The doc comment even undersells it:\n\n```\n/// Format: [type_byte][payload][8-byte TTL-ms or 0][2-byte CRC placeholder]\n```\n\n(Actual format: 8-byte TTL, 1-byte version tag = 10, 8-byte CRC64 — so the doc comment is stale: we do write a real 8-byte CRC64 using the Redis polynomial, not a 2-byte placeholder. That part is fine.)\n\nThe deeper problem: the type bytes are flat {0=string, 1=list, 2=set, 4=hash, 5=sortedset, 15=stream} with raw-length encoding and raw-bytes payloads. Upstream RDB uses encoding-specific type tags (`RDB_TYPE_STRING`=0 with LZF or raw subtag, `RDB_TYPE_SET_INTSET`=11, `RDB_TYPE_HASH_ZIPLIST`=13, `RDB_TYPE_LIST_QUICKLIST_2`=18, `RDB_TYPE_STREAM_LISTPACKS_3`=21, etc.). Our encoding is upstream-incompatible across EVERY type.\n\nConsequence: a client that `DUMP`s a key from FrankenRedis and `RESTORE`s into upstream Redis gets `ERR DUMP payload version or checksum are wrong` because the version byte 10 doesn't match upstream's version-field semantic (upstream gates on `rdbVersion == supported_range`, which our `10` superficially satisfies — but the payload parser fails on unknown type bytes and \\\"wrong\\\" length encoding even before the version check). Symmetrically, upstream DUMP output can't be restored into FrankenRedis — `restore_key` at lib.rs:9547 only recognizes our type bytes {0,1,2,4,5,15}.\n\n**Impact on `MIGRATE`:** MIGRATE uses DUMP + RESTORE as its wire format. A `MIGRATE` from FrankenRedis to a real Redis node fails; the reverse too. Clustered operations are therefore fundamentally broken at the data-transfer layer, even before the cluster-admin bead (`frankenredis-jsr7`).\n\n## Distinguishing from frankenredis-s5su\n\n`frankenredis-s5su` covers **RDB file format** for streams specifically (type 15 inside .rdb files). This bead covers **DUMP/RESTORE wire format** for ALL types (strings, lists, sets, hashes, sorted sets, streams) — a different binary blob that flows inside a single RESP BulkString over the network, used by MIGRATE and by direct DUMP/RESTORE commands.\n\nThere is some overlap in infrastructure (both need to speak upstream's type-tag matrix), but the file-format ingestion from disk and the wire-format ingestion from MIGRATE take different code paths in upstream Redis too, and we should track them separately.\n\n## Applying /testing-conformance-harnesses (Pattern 3: cross-impl round-trip)\n\n- Corpus: for each upstream-supported Redis type + each upstream-supported encoding variant, capture `DUMP` output from vendored `redis-server` and store under `crates/fr-store/tests/fixtures/dump_roundtrip/`.\n- Gate 1: our `restore_key` must accept every fixture without error.\n- Gate 2: after RESTORE into our store, re-DUMP; feed that DUMP bytes to upstream `redis-server` and ask it to RESTORE; then query the key on upstream; canonicalize and compare to the original upstream state.\n- Gate 3: the reverse direction — seed our store, DUMP, feed to upstream, read the key on upstream, canonicalize, compare to our in-memory value.\n\n## Applying /testing-fuzzing\n\n- `fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_dump_restore.rs` exists but is self-referential (roundtrip inside FrankenRedis only). Retarget it as **differential**: `arbitrary::Arbitrary` → generate a Value, DUMP via ours, RESTORE via upstream (if present), verify roundtrip through both directions. Today this fuzzer passes because it never checks upstream; once real, it surfaces every type where our encoding diverges.\n\n## Fix scope\n\n- `fr-store::dump_key`: switch to upstream RDB type tags + encoding-aware serialization (reuse `fr-persist::rdb::*` helpers; they already encode full RDB records).\n- `fr-store::restore_key`: dispatch on upstream type tags; reject our legacy types {1,2,4,5,15} with a one-release deprecation warning OR (better, given AGENTS.md \\\"no backwards-compatibility shims\\\") hard-remove them and regenerate any persisted .rdb fixtures in-tree.\n- DUMP version tag must follow the upstream-compatible supported range (`RDB_VERSION` 11 for Redis 7.2.x, 12 for 7.4.x). Pick the one the vendored `legacy_redis_code/redis` targets and pin.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- `DUMP ... → RESTORE ...` succeeds byte-identically across (FrankenRedis → FrankenRedis), (FrankenRedis → upstream), (upstream → FrankenRedis) for every upstream-observable type/encoding pair.\n- `MIGRATE` from FrankenRedis to upstream moves a key successfully (observed via `GET`/`HGETALL`/etc. on the destination).\n- `fuzz_dump_restore` retargeted differential-mode runs 1M iterations against the vendored oracle with zero mismatches outside documented XFAILs.\n\n## Labels\n\nfr-store, dump, restore, migrate, rdb-format-divergence, conformance-gap, mock-finder","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T03:55:57.306722763Z","created_by":"cc-redis","updated_at":"2026-04-23T03:55:57.306722763Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance-gap","dump","fr-store","migrate","mock-finder","rdb-format-divergence","restore"]}
